# **ğŸ§ Linux Commands Cheat Sheet :-**

## **File & Directory Operations :-**

* `ls` â€“ List files in current directory.
    
* `ls -l` â€“ Long listing format.
    
* `ls -a` â€“ Show hidden files.
    
* `cd <dir>` â€“ Change directory.
    
* `pwd` â€“ Print current directory path.
    
* `mkdir <dir>` â€“ Create new directory.
    
* `rmdir <dir>` â€“ Remove empty directory.
    
* `rm <file>` â€“ Remove file.
    
* `rm -r <dir>` â€“ Remove directory with contents.
    
* `cp <src> <dest>` â€“ Copy file/directory.
    
* `mv <src> <dest>` â€“ Move/rename file/directory.
    

## **File Viewing & Editing :-**

* `cat <file>` â€“ View file contents.
    
* `less <file>` â€“ View file with scroll.
    
* `head <file>` â€“ First 10 lines of file.
    
* `tail <file>` â€“ Last 10 lines of file.
    
* `nano <file>` â€“ Edit file using nano.
    
* `vim <file>` â€“ Edit file using vim.
    

## **File Searching :-**

* `find <dir> -name <filename>` â€“ Find file by name.
    
* `grep "<text>" <file>` â€“ Search text in file.
    
* `grep -r "<text>" <dir>` â€“ Recursively search in directory.
    

## **File Permissions :-**

* `chmod +x <file>` â€“ Make file executable.
    
* `chmod 755 <file>` â€“ Set read/write/execute for owner, read/execute for others.
    
* `chown user:group <file>` â€“ Change file ownership.
    

## **System Info :-**

* `uname -a` â€“ Kernel version.
    
* `top` â€“ Real-time system processes.
    
* `df -h` â€“ Disk usage.
    
* `free -h` â€“ RAM usage.
    
* `uptime` â€“ System uptime.
    
* `whoami` â€“ Current user.
    

## **Package Management :-**

* `sudo apt update` â€“ Update package list.
    
* `sudo apt upgrade` â€“ Upgrade packages.
    
* `sudo apt install <package>` â€“ Install package.
    
* `sudo apt remove <package>` â€“ Remove package.
    

# **ğŸ™ Git Commands Cheat Sheet :-**

## **Configuration :-**

* `git config --global` [`user.name`](http://user.name) `"Your Name"` â€“ Set Git username.
    
* `git config --global` [`user.email`](http://user.email) `"`[`you@example.com`](mailto:you@example.com)`"` â€“ Set Git email.
    
* `git config --list` â€“ List config.
    

## **Repository Management :-**

* `git init` â€“ Initialize new Git repo.
    
* `git clone <url>` â€“ Clone remote repo.
    
* `git status` â€“ Show repo status.
    
* `git log` â€“ Show commit history.
    
* `git diff` â€“ Show changes.
    

## **Staging & Committing :-**

* `git add <file>` â€“ Stage file.
    
* `git add .` â€“ Stage all changes.
    
* `git commit -m "message"` â€“ Commit with message.
    
* `git commit -am "message"` â€“ Add & commit tracked files.
    

## **Branching :-**

* `git branch` â€“ List branches.
    
* `git branch <name>` â€“ Create branch.
    
* `git checkout <name>` â€“ Switch branch.
    
* `git checkout -b <name>` â€“ Create and switch to new branch.
    
* `git merge <branch>` â€“ Merge branch into current.
    

## **Remote Repositories :-**

* `git remote -v` â€“ Show remote URLs.
    
* `git push origin <branch>` â€“ Push changes.
    
* `git pull` â€“ Pull latest changes.
    
* `git fetch` â€“ Download changes.
    

## **Undoing Changes :-**

* `git reset <file>` â€“ Unstage file.
    
* `git checkout -- <file>` â€“ Discard file changes.
    
* `git revert <commit>` â€“ Revert a commit.
    
* `git reset --hard <commit>` â€“ Reset to commit.
